column5: Dang now them are two great reports thanks for taking the time to share
Great report
Thanks Mike! We will be on Cameron Lake. Ive never fished Oba lake myself. I am staying in the big town of Oba tho....I think the population is under 10 now...
Wow!
Awesome!! Just simply AWESOME!!!
Loved both reports Tyler    AWESOME dude Thanks for posting Jacques
As usual, Dunn right awesome!great report mate.
Thanks Tyler for the taking the time to put together all those wicked photos. Seeing pics of my old stomping grounds brings back a ton of great memories.
No problem...my pleasure actually... I get to read a ton of great reports on this forum....  Just trying to return the gesture!  Thanks again to all!  TDunn
I hate you! not really... well maybe a little.

Fished another lake for walleye/perch/pike.  We hit some nice fish and took back some good eats for the night!                    On our way home we hit the Nipigon River for a couple hours. Mixed bag for us there!  A few lakers, a few OOS eyes, whitie,  brookie and a bow!            An amazing trip all around!!! I will be back sooner than later!!!  Now its time to get ready for walleyes! Heading up to Oba, Ontario to guide walleyes for 2 weeks! Can't wait!  Hope you all enjoyed!   TDunn
Yup, enjoyed both.  Great reports and thanks for sharing.
Wow!  Waited til I read part two to comment.  Some amazing fishing adventures there.  Loved all the pics...some great scenery shots in there!
wow !!! amazing trip you guys did great !!!!
that is some great fishing
Man that looks like a great trip.  Thanks for taking the time to post all of those photos!
Excellent report Tyler and friends. Thank you for that. Where are you guiding in Oba? Kabinakagami?
^^^ Ya.  What he said!
Awesome report! I always look forward to your reports...this did not disapoint! Thankss for posting... HH
awesome part 2 ... thanks for posting the great pictures

Hey Roy!  Nope not Kaby but I have fished that lake. I was a dockhand there 10 years ago!   I'll be here  http://www.ontarionorthfishing.com/  I fished the lake in 2007 and 2008.....a million walleye in the lake! Can't wait!!  thanks to all for the great comments!  TDunn
Truly enjoyed both parts. Your a lucky man.  Thanks for taking the time to share.
Thats just fantastic fishing...Part II easily as good as part I!  Those whitefish are tanks! I love fishing whities!
Very nice Tyler. Both reports.
I always look forward to the TDunn quarterly.   Great stuff!
Well done! Thanks for sharing.
Absolutely awesome stuff!  Live it!  Cheers.
Great report. Love the variety of species in the Nip.
WOW! What a great multi species trip. Great report. Thanks for sharing
Drop me the link here to part 1.  Think I might have missed it.  Great fishing dood!  Always enjoy your reports.
HATEHATEHATE!!!!
What a great multi-species adventure.  Both parts.  I almost moved to the Soo about 16 years ago. Love the fishing there.
awesome report nice eyes
Awesome Tyler, just awesome!  Had no idea the fishing on Oba was quite that good. Have fun up there, I'll be looking forward to your report.   Cheers
